WEBVTT

00:40.457 --> 00:43.376
ALL CHARACTERS, PLACES, GROUPS, AND
ORGANIZATIONS IN THIS WORK ARE FICTITIOUS

00:43.460 --> 00:46.379
SCENES WITH ANIMALS ARE STAGED
ACCORDING TO ANIMAL WELFARE GUIDELINES

00:51.676 --> 00:54.220
Yeo-reum. Are you asleep?

00:55.805 --> 00:56.806
No.

00:59.434 --> 01:00.643
Are you not sleepy?

01:02.103 --> 01:03.104
No.

01:04.105 --> 01:05.273
Yeo-reum.

01:05.356 --> 01:09.444
There's something I wish for every night
before I sleep, looking at the ceiling.

01:10.820 --> 01:13.740
"When I wake up tomorrow,

01:13.823 --> 01:15.784
please let me see a different ceiling."

01:16.534 --> 01:18.953
"Please let me wake up ten years later."

01:20.538 --> 01:21.414
Ten years?

01:22.248 --> 01:23.291
Don't you think that's a waste?

01:23.958 --> 01:25.627
No, not at all.

01:27.670 --> 01:30.632
How do you want things to be in ten years?

01:32.342 --> 01:36.012
First of all,
I definitely want to be rich.

01:38.056 --> 01:39.849
What do you want to do with the money?

01:41.601 --> 01:44.145
I'm going to buy Grandma an apartment.

01:44.229 --> 01:45.271
And…

01:45.814 --> 01:48.066
I'll send her on a trip to China.

01:48.566 --> 01:51.152
You'd have to be really rich for that.

01:53.696 --> 01:56.366
What about me? What will you do for me?

02:00.745 --> 02:02.831
Maybe I'll become rich in my next life.

02:02.914 --> 02:04.749
What a lousy answer.

02:06.334 --> 02:10.380
What about you?
If you were to wake up after 10 years,

02:10.463 --> 02:12.090
what would you want to do?

02:13.133 --> 02:14.801
I'd be 38 years old.

02:16.511 --> 02:18.179
Does it have to be in the future?

02:18.263 --> 02:19.305
What?

02:19.389 --> 02:21.641
Would you rather go back to the past?

02:22.225 --> 02:23.309
Yes.

02:26.437 --> 02:28.231
Once when I was young,

02:29.607 --> 02:32.443
I woke up in the middle of the night

02:33.027 --> 02:34.571
when I was sleeping with my parents.

02:35.113 --> 02:40.076
We were in the middle
of a big thunderstorm,

02:40.660 --> 02:43.079
but strangely, I wasn't scared at all.

02:43.913 --> 02:45.039
It just…

02:47.625 --> 02:49.544
It felt so nice and cozy.

02:51.170 --> 02:53.590
I still remember
how the blanket felt that night.

02:59.888 --> 03:01.598
Do you have any moments like this?

03:05.560 --> 03:06.895
I couldn't have one.

03:09.314 --> 03:13.151
Anyway, thank you so much for today.

03:13.818 --> 03:15.695
Thank you for letting me crash here

03:17.238 --> 03:20.283
and for not asking what happened.

03:22.160 --> 03:23.369
I'm thankful too.

03:24.704 --> 03:26.581
You don't ask me questions like,

03:26.664 --> 03:29.834
"Why are you here?"
"Why are you lazing around, not working?"

03:33.755 --> 03:36.758
I hope you'll be happy to see this ceiling

03:37.342 --> 03:39.093
when you wake up tomorrow.

03:44.891 --> 03:46.017
Good night.

03:47.185 --> 03:48.645
You too.

05:14.689 --> 05:17.150
Gosh. You're home, Bom.

05:18.651 --> 05:20.695
Where have you been all night?

05:21.612 --> 05:23.031
You didn't answer your phone.

05:23.531 --> 05:25.283
My phone was turned off.

05:25.366 --> 05:27.952
Why were you sleeping here?

05:28.953 --> 05:30.204
Did you eat?

05:31.789 --> 05:32.790
Where's Dad?

05:33.374 --> 05:35.126
He went out last night
and hasn't come back.

05:35.877 --> 05:38.129
He must be upset too.

05:40.006 --> 05:41.007
Bom.

05:42.050 --> 05:44.093
No matter how much you hate him,
he's still your dad.

05:44.177 --> 05:45.887
Grandma. I'm hungry.

05:46.471 --> 05:47.555
Right. Of course.

05:47.638 --> 05:49.849
I'll make breakfast for you.

05:57.231 --> 05:59.400
You motherfuckers,
do you think I'm a pushover?

06:13.498 --> 06:15.541
WARD NUMBER 2

06:15.625 --> 06:16.751
Goodness.

06:18.461 --> 06:19.837
Ma'am.

06:21.464 --> 06:23.716
Where's Bom?

06:24.342 --> 06:26.886
She's having surgery in that room.

06:27.470 --> 06:28.763
What happened?

06:29.263 --> 06:30.556
I don't…

06:31.933 --> 06:34.435
My poor baby…

06:42.235 --> 06:43.319
Ma'am.

06:52.662 --> 06:54.122
Gosh, I feel sick.

06:55.373 --> 06:56.374
Dae-bum.

06:58.918 --> 07:00.002
Dae-bum.

07:07.844 --> 07:10.346
Darn it. I'm late.

07:13.641 --> 07:15.309
SEONG-MAN

07:18.146 --> 07:19.230
What do you want?

07:19.814 --> 07:20.815
Hello?

07:20.898 --> 07:22.900
Hey, where are you right now?

07:22.984 --> 07:24.861
Where would I be? I'm at Dae-bum's.

07:25.361 --> 07:27.321
So you really slept over there?

07:27.905 --> 07:30.491
I know Dae-bum is harmless,
but you're still a girl.

07:30.575 --> 07:32.076
That's really not appropriate.

07:32.160 --> 07:34.620
Why do you care if I sleep at Dae-bum's

07:34.704 --> 07:36.747
-or at a motel?
-What did you say?

07:36.831 --> 07:39.667
Why would you sleep at a motel
when you have a house?

07:39.750 --> 07:42.295
Just shut up. Hang up.
I need to take a shower.

07:42.378 --> 07:45.465
A shower? Hey, Ji-yeong. Hold on.

07:45.548 --> 07:47.175
Go home and shower.

07:49.510 --> 07:50.553
So annoying.

07:51.137 --> 07:52.889
Why would she shower there?

07:56.058 --> 07:57.310
The person you are trying to reach…

07:57.393 --> 07:59.687
This is driving me nuts. Did she block me?

07:59.770 --> 08:01.230
RETURNED BOOKS SHELF

08:01.314 --> 08:03.357
Dae-bum, when does Bom usually come here?

08:03.941 --> 08:05.443
I'm not really sure.

08:06.027 --> 08:07.778
You're terrible at keeping track.

08:08.362 --> 08:11.491
The only people who come here
are Bom and Yeo-reum.

08:17.246 --> 08:18.164
Hello.

08:18.247 --> 08:20.500
-I'll leave it here.
-Thank you.

08:23.002 --> 08:24.295
What about Yeo-reum?

08:24.378 --> 08:25.713
She'll be here soon.

08:27.173 --> 08:29.425
So you keep track of when Yeo-reum comes.

08:29.509 --> 08:31.344
Are you playing favorites right now?

08:33.721 --> 08:35.056
Dae-bum, let's go hang out!

08:35.139 --> 08:36.015
Let's play!

08:37.099 --> 08:39.393
Hey, guys. You promised
not to act like this.

08:39.477 --> 08:40.895
Treat him with more respect.

08:40.978 --> 08:42.980
That feels so awkward though.

08:43.064 --> 08:44.232
Yes, it's weird.

08:44.315 --> 08:45.525
Then practice.

08:45.608 --> 08:47.652
-What's wrong with him?
-Guys, heads-up.

08:47.735 --> 08:48.861
-Mine!
-Nice!

08:48.945 --> 08:51.239
-Give it here.
-Why are you taking the ball?

08:51.322 --> 08:52.573
What are you doing?

08:54.158 --> 08:55.409
Dae-bum.

08:55.493 --> 08:56.869
What's up, Jun?

08:56.953 --> 08:58.287
-Listen.
-Okay.

08:58.371 --> 09:01.332
I heard Dad on the phone
while I was eating,

09:01.415 --> 09:03.501
and someone is in operation at a hospital.

09:04.085 --> 09:05.002
Who?

09:05.086 --> 09:06.045
Was it Bom?

09:06.587 --> 09:08.047
No, was it Yeo-reum?

09:08.130 --> 09:09.757
-What?
-I'm not sure.

09:09.840 --> 09:12.134
One of them got hurt really badly.

09:13.261 --> 09:14.637
Wait for just a second here.

09:15.513 --> 09:17.056
Hey, what did you just say?

09:17.139 --> 09:19.016
Which one of them got hurt?

09:19.100 --> 09:20.017
It's not Bom, is it?

09:20.101 --> 09:21.352
-Is it?
-I don't know.

09:21.435 --> 09:22.395
Dae-bum!

09:29.777 --> 09:31.404
You can stay seated.

09:32.405 --> 09:34.865
The operation was a success.

09:35.366 --> 09:38.035
Her liver was slightly damaged,
so we had it sutured.

09:38.119 --> 09:41.581
Fortunately, the injury wasn't fatal,
so she's not in any danger.

09:41.664 --> 09:43.833
Thank you so much, sir.

09:43.916 --> 09:45.459
-You must've been startled.
-Yes.

09:45.543 --> 09:48.504
She'll have to be hospitalized
for about 10 days.

09:48.588 --> 09:49.422
Okay.

09:50.006 --> 09:51.799
When can she start eating?

09:51.882 --> 09:54.135
The hospital will give her dinner
starting today.

09:54.760 --> 09:58.556
So how did she get injured?

09:59.098 --> 10:00.725
-Well, actually…
-What?

10:01.684 --> 10:03.102
We're not so sure.

10:03.185 --> 10:04.937
The insurance coverage will vary

10:05.021 --> 10:06.897
between an accidental injury
and a self-inflicted one.

10:06.981 --> 10:08.899
It may end up involving the police.

10:08.983 --> 10:11.110
So please let us know
when the patient wakes up.

10:11.193 --> 10:13.154
-The police?
-Okay.

10:13.821 --> 10:14.905
I will.

10:18.367 --> 10:20.745
What did the nurse just say?

10:20.828 --> 10:22.705
I just don't get it.

10:23.664 --> 10:24.790
Grandma.

10:24.874 --> 10:27.752
When others ask what happened,
just say you don't know.

10:29.712 --> 10:31.672
Dad might go to prison for this.

10:31.756 --> 10:34.383
What do you mean he might go to prison?

10:34.467 --> 10:36.969
It's not like he did this on purpose.

10:38.346 --> 10:39.347
Mr. Librarian.

10:43.559 --> 10:44.810
Ms. Lee.

10:45.645 --> 10:46.562
Bom.

10:47.146 --> 10:49.148
Bom!

10:49.899 --> 10:52.401
What happened to you?

10:52.485 --> 10:54.445
You shouldn't be waking her up.

10:55.363 --> 10:57.448
Bom!

10:58.449 --> 11:00.743
How did you find out?

11:01.744 --> 11:03.829
Jun told me at the library.

11:05.414 --> 11:08.167
Bom will be okay, right?

11:08.793 --> 11:09.794
Yes.

11:10.294 --> 11:14.048
The operation went well,
and the wound isn't deep.

11:21.931 --> 11:25.810
I heard you were with Ji-yeong
until late last night.

11:26.310 --> 11:27.395
Yes.

11:31.315 --> 11:32.817
Ms. Cho…

11:34.235 --> 11:36.737
She was very worried about you.

11:41.951 --> 11:44.328
Shouldn't you be going now?

11:44.954 --> 11:45.955
I should.

11:48.040 --> 11:49.083
Then…

11:49.959 --> 11:53.003
I'll let Bom know you stopped by
when she wakes up.

12:00.761 --> 12:02.972
Ma'am, you should wear these.

12:04.265 --> 12:05.808
Gosh, thank you so much.

12:09.687 --> 12:10.855
Thank you.

12:12.773 --> 12:14.733
Yeo-reum, did Dae-bum leave?

12:15.276 --> 12:16.110
Yes.

12:16.193 --> 12:19.029
He rushed over here like a madman earlier.

12:19.113 --> 12:21.115
A kid came to the library

12:21.198 --> 12:23.701
and told us either you or Bom were hurt.

12:24.410 --> 12:26.537
I almost passed out keeping up with him.

12:28.080 --> 12:29.123
I see.

12:29.665 --> 12:30.708
It seems like…

12:31.917 --> 12:33.294
it was Bom.

12:37.673 --> 12:39.633
-Ha-neul.
-Grandma.

12:40.217 --> 12:41.385
Come sit here.

12:41.969 --> 12:43.888
Can we talk outside?

12:43.971 --> 12:46.015
Sure.

12:58.569 --> 13:00.905
If we say that she did this to herself,

13:01.447 --> 13:03.073
it'll be considered self-inflicted.

13:03.574 --> 13:06.076
Then the insurance
won't cover the hospital fee.

13:07.703 --> 13:08.746
Do you by any chance

13:09.455 --> 13:11.373
know how much the hospital bill will be?

13:11.999 --> 13:14.001
Including her one-week stay
at the hospital,

13:15.544 --> 13:17.505
it's over 10 million won.

13:17.588 --> 13:18.756
Ten million won?

13:20.049 --> 13:22.009
What do you mean by that?

13:22.092 --> 13:24.470
Explain it in simple words.

13:25.846 --> 13:27.973
If we say that Dad did it,

13:28.891 --> 13:31.101
we'll pay less than two million
with the insurance.

13:31.936 --> 13:35.439
But Dad will end up getting arrested.

13:42.988 --> 13:44.615
Let's say I hurt her.

13:44.698 --> 13:46.909
I'll tell them I hurt her,

13:46.992 --> 13:49.578
-and I'll go to prison instead.
-Grandma.

13:49.662 --> 13:52.456
What are you talking about?
No one will believe you.

13:52.540 --> 13:55.042
But your dad will get arrested.

13:55.543 --> 13:57.962
I can't let that happen.

13:58.629 --> 13:59.838
Ha-neul.

14:00.339 --> 14:03.050
Ha-neul.

14:03.133 --> 14:04.343
Ma'am.

14:04.426 --> 14:06.262
ANGOK PUBLIC LIBRARY

14:07.221 --> 14:08.639
-Hey!
-Hey!

14:08.722 --> 14:10.099
RETURNED BOOKS SHELF

14:10.182 --> 14:11.100
-Yes!
-Hey!

14:11.183 --> 14:13.852
Stop messing around
and put all the books back in!

14:15.104 --> 14:16.689
This one? Where?

14:17.314 --> 14:18.857
Just put it anywhere!

14:18.941 --> 14:20.442
Hey, stop it!

14:20.526 --> 14:22.194
-Stop it!
-Anywhere!

14:22.945 --> 14:24.780
Stop that!

14:24.864 --> 14:27.074
Hey! What are you kids doing?

14:27.157 --> 14:29.201
Get over here!

14:30.160 --> 14:31.203
Darn it.

14:32.705 --> 14:34.081
Where did Dae-bum go?

14:34.164 --> 14:35.499
He went to the hospital.

14:35.583 --> 14:37.877
Hospital? Why? When?

14:37.960 --> 14:39.628
Bom and Yeo-reum got hurt,

14:39.712 --> 14:41.380
so the two guys rushed over there.

14:41.463 --> 14:42.923
Really?

14:43.007 --> 14:44.216
Where and how badly hurt are they?

14:45.050 --> 14:47.511
You shouldn't be chatting in the library.

14:49.471 --> 14:50.764
Hurry up and clean this up.

14:51.682 --> 14:53.017
Don't run. Get over here.

14:53.100 --> 14:54.935
Hey. Come over here, guys.

14:55.019 --> 14:58.439
I can't keep my voice down
with these kids.

14:58.522 --> 14:59.690
Here you go.

15:00.524 --> 15:01.692
Guys, wait!

15:11.619 --> 15:12.912
Hey, Bom!

15:14.872 --> 15:16.123
-Hello.
-Hello, Seong-min.

15:16.206 --> 15:17.958
What happened to you, Bom?

15:20.502 --> 15:21.962
Is she going to be okay?

15:22.046 --> 15:24.298
The surgery went well, so she'll be fine.

15:27.551 --> 15:30.846
Why does she have to go through
such a hard time?

15:31.388 --> 15:32.723
Goodness.

15:35.225 --> 15:37.561
Seong-min. Why are you crying?

15:38.520 --> 15:40.856
He's been tenderhearted
since when he was a kid.

15:42.107 --> 15:44.401
Seong-min, it's okay.

15:44.485 --> 15:47.029
Her surgery went well. She'll be fine.

15:48.697 --> 15:50.407
Can I ask you a favor?

15:50.991 --> 15:54.536
I have to drop by my house
after I feed her dinner.

15:54.620 --> 15:58.332
I panicked and rushed out in the morning,
so I couldn't bring anything with me.

15:58.415 --> 15:59.917
Can you watch her until I'm back?

16:00.501 --> 16:03.003
I could just stay with her today.

16:03.087 --> 16:06.507
Gosh, no. It's fine.
You've already stayed for so long.

16:06.590 --> 16:07.758
Ma'am.

16:07.841 --> 16:10.386
Then I'll give you a ride home

16:10.469 --> 16:12.096
and drop Yeo-reum off on the way.

16:12.638 --> 16:14.932
Would you do that for us? Thank you.

16:18.644 --> 16:21.271
It'll be uncomfortable
sleeping in a hospital.

16:21.355 --> 16:23.023
I'll be okay.

16:23.107 --> 16:25.526
I should be next to Bom when she wakes up.

16:26.527 --> 16:29.071
I'm letting you stay with her
just for today then.

16:29.780 --> 16:32.658
Thank you for everything.

16:33.409 --> 16:34.910
You even bought me slippers.

16:35.703 --> 16:38.122
You're a very considerate young lady.

16:43.293 --> 16:45.129
Don't worry too much.

16:46.880 --> 16:48.882
I don't know what to do.

16:49.466 --> 16:52.553
Bom is my granddaughter.

16:54.513 --> 16:56.056
Her dad is my son.

16:58.976 --> 17:00.686
How could such a thing have happened?

17:22.958 --> 17:24.877
Why are you outside?

17:26.211 --> 17:27.421
You must be hungry.

17:28.005 --> 17:29.423
I'll make you something.

17:30.007 --> 17:31.091
What about Bom?

17:32.134 --> 17:34.261
The operation went well.

17:35.220 --> 17:36.847
-Mom.
-Yes?

17:37.931 --> 17:40.017
I want to get treated.

17:41.685 --> 17:42.686
What do you mean?

17:43.562 --> 17:45.439
I want to quit drinking.

17:45.939 --> 17:47.024
All right.

17:47.775 --> 17:49.693
You should stop drinking.

17:50.360 --> 17:52.780
All you need to do is quit drinking.

17:52.863 --> 17:54.406
-Seong-man.
-Yes?

17:55.699 --> 17:57.493
Can you give me a ride to the hospital?

17:58.410 --> 18:00.871
Jeong-hun. That's a great decision.

18:00.954 --> 18:02.706
It really is.

18:02.790 --> 18:06.126
All right. Let's eat first then.

18:06.877 --> 18:08.712
You've made the right decision.

18:08.796 --> 18:11.799
I'll look into a hospital and everything.

18:11.882 --> 18:15.677
The hospital can treat you
and make you whole again.

18:15.761 --> 18:16.970
You'll be all right.

18:33.445 --> 18:34.905
You must have been starving.

18:38.075 --> 18:40.202
You're so good.

18:40.285 --> 18:41.870
You didn't even poop all day.

18:42.621 --> 18:44.331
Let's go for a walk after.

18:50.963 --> 18:52.172
Hey, Mr. Librarian.

18:52.256 --> 18:54.591
I thought you were at the hospital.

18:55.634 --> 18:58.387
Bom's grandmother said
she'll stay with her today.

19:01.515 --> 19:03.892
You must have been walking your dog.

19:03.976 --> 19:07.646
Yes. Gyeo-ul has been alone all day today.

19:09.064 --> 19:11.650
Gyeo-ul as in winter
and Yeo-reum as in summer?

19:14.027 --> 19:16.029
I didn't name the dog.

19:16.113 --> 19:17.656
Bom named him.

19:18.824 --> 19:19.867
I see.

19:24.371 --> 19:27.916
Were you on your way home
from the library?

19:32.713 --> 19:34.715
I wanted to give you these.

19:35.465 --> 19:36.508
What are they?

19:36.592 --> 19:39.428
I figured you'd be too busy
to come to the library, so…

19:42.848 --> 19:43.932
Thank you.

19:44.892 --> 19:48.604
Will you be going to visit Bom
every day at the hospital?

19:48.687 --> 19:50.522
Yes, that's what I'm planning.

19:56.069 --> 19:59.990
Do you want me to take care of Gyeo-ul?

20:00.490 --> 20:01.491
Sorry?

20:01.992 --> 20:04.286
He can stay in the library yard
during the day.

20:04.870 --> 20:06.079
I mean…

20:08.874 --> 20:13.170
But you can't take him
inside the hospital.

20:22.346 --> 20:23.388
Come here.

20:28.393 --> 20:29.478
Ahn Dae-bum.

20:30.062 --> 20:30.938
Professor.

20:31.521 --> 20:33.065
I got here too late, didn't I?

20:33.148 --> 20:35.567
Professor. How did you find me here?

20:35.651 --> 20:37.027
That lady told me.

20:37.110 --> 20:41.031
You live such a wonderful life.
How do you live without a phone?

20:41.782 --> 20:44.243
The home takes after you.

20:45.118 --> 20:46.620
It's quite bland.

20:48.038 --> 20:50.832
Goodness. You even raise a dog.

20:52.584 --> 20:53.669
Dae-bum.

20:54.378 --> 20:57.923
Aren't you curious
why I suddenly came to see you?

20:59.216 --> 21:00.550
Hawking radiation.

21:01.301 --> 21:03.303
Penrose–Hawking singularity theorems.

21:03.387 --> 21:07.516
Isn't it cool to have a theory
that's named after you?

21:07.599 --> 21:08.725
-Wait.
-Professor.

21:08.809 --> 21:09.977
Hold on.

21:15.023 --> 21:15.857
Look, Professor.

21:15.941 --> 21:17.567
-Give me a second.
-Please.

21:21.446 --> 21:24.533
For the first time in Korean history,
we'll be naming a formula.

21:25.033 --> 21:27.077
You said this formula was correct,

21:27.160 --> 21:29.746
and I thought it was wrong.

21:29.830 --> 21:32.082
No, I was convinced
that it had to be wrong.

21:33.041 --> 21:34.167
Last month,

21:36.420 --> 21:38.505
Professor Holland presented this.

21:39.423 --> 21:41.466
Apparently, you're right and I'm wrong.

21:43.635 --> 21:44.636
The thing is,

21:45.137 --> 21:49.308
Holland only proved it partially.
It's incomplete.

21:50.183 --> 21:51.310
What do you say?

21:51.935 --> 21:54.021
Let's prove this formula together.

21:54.104 --> 21:55.856
Let's shock the world with this.

21:55.939 --> 21:56.898
Professor.

21:56.982 --> 21:59.526
-Professor, I'm sorry, but…
-I get it.

22:00.360 --> 22:01.570
Don't answer right away.

22:02.154 --> 22:03.822
Just give it a serious thought.

22:04.364 --> 22:06.408
You've been away for a while.

22:07.659 --> 22:09.703
Give this a read when you're bored.

22:13.290 --> 22:14.791
Why do I have to do that?

22:15.292 --> 22:18.003
That'll never happen.
I'll never forgive him!

22:19.379 --> 22:20.714
Please, Bom.

22:21.298 --> 22:23.383
Can't you do it for me, Bom?

22:23.967 --> 22:26.803
I'm going to tell the truth!

22:26.887 --> 22:28.013
You can't.

22:29.306 --> 22:32.350
You can't. If you do, your dad…

22:32.434 --> 22:36.104
No. I don't want to!
Why do I have to do that for him?

22:36.188 --> 22:38.231
Bom, your stitches are going to come out.

22:38.315 --> 22:40.776
Tell him to rot in prison!

22:40.859 --> 22:42.986
Tell the cops to arrest him!

22:43.070 --> 22:46.198
I just want him dead!

22:46.281 --> 22:48.283
You're always so self-centered.

22:48.366 --> 22:50.243
How do you think Grandma will feel
if Dad goes to jail?

22:50.327 --> 22:53.789
Do you think I care?
It's none of my business.

22:53.872 --> 22:55.832
So everyone can just rot in hell!

22:55.916 --> 22:58.460
-Why should I do that for him?
-Kim Bom!

22:59.086 --> 23:01.129
How can you say that
in front of your grandmother?

23:15.185 --> 23:17.687
-Here, drink this.
-Thank you.

23:19.397 --> 23:21.650
She's just not herself right now.

23:22.567 --> 23:23.819
-I understand.
-Right.

23:25.654 --> 23:27.447
I'm sorry to ask,

23:28.406 --> 23:31.409
but can you please come with me?

23:31.493 --> 23:32.661
Of course.

23:34.037 --> 23:35.872
-Give me your paw!
-Sit!

23:35.956 --> 23:38.041
-He gave me his paw!
-No way!

23:38.125 --> 23:40.335
-He did the shake!
-Give me your paw!

23:40.418 --> 23:43.255
You even brought a dog to the library now?

23:43.338 --> 23:44.464
So what?

23:44.548 --> 23:45.799
-So what?
-Whatever.

23:45.882 --> 23:47.425
Do you not hear me?

23:47.509 --> 23:49.636
You can't bring dogs to the library.

23:49.719 --> 23:52.347
-Hey!
-Stop it.

23:52.430 --> 23:53.765
-Get him out.
-No.

23:53.849 --> 23:55.392
How is he doing?

23:55.475 --> 23:58.019
-Dae-bum, what's his name?
-Gyeo-ul.

23:58.103 --> 24:00.272
-"Gyeo-ul"?
-Hey, Gyeo-ul.

24:00.355 --> 24:02.566
Hey, Dae-bum. What's going on?

24:02.649 --> 24:05.068
-I'm looking after him for the time being.
-So cute.

24:05.152 --> 24:06.820
-You are?
-It's delicious, right?

24:06.903 --> 24:09.573
-Whose dog is it?
-You have to pet him gently like this.

24:09.656 --> 24:10.615
He's cute, isn't he?

24:12.909 --> 24:14.327
He's so soft.

24:19.166 --> 24:20.375
KO HYE-RIM
BANK TELLER

24:20.458 --> 24:22.752
Please fill out the highlighted items.

24:25.422 --> 24:28.258
Here, where it's highlighted.

24:29.843 --> 24:31.178
LOAN REQUEST FORM

24:33.638 --> 24:35.098
It's hard to read, right?

24:35.182 --> 24:36.975
I'll fill it out for you.

24:37.058 --> 24:38.977
Would you do that for me?

24:39.811 --> 24:42.314
There's a magnifying glass
near the entrance.

24:42.397 --> 24:44.858
It's fine. I can fill it out for her.

24:46.359 --> 24:48.153
It's Jung Yeong-suk.

24:50.238 --> 24:53.658
How much loan can she take out?

24:53.742 --> 24:55.076
Let me see.

24:55.744 --> 24:57.329
LOAN CONSULTATION

24:57.412 --> 24:58.538
What the…

24:58.622 --> 24:59.456
Ma'am.

24:59.956 --> 25:01.458
How do you expect to take out another loan

25:01.541 --> 25:03.793
when you have this much set in collateral?

25:03.877 --> 25:07.214
I'm sure my son paid that off
a long time ago.

25:07.297 --> 25:08.757
What do you mean?

25:09.257 --> 25:11.801
We can't approve more loans like this.

25:11.885 --> 25:13.929
You've already reached the limit.

25:23.188 --> 25:25.815
Yeo-reum asks for your help a lot.

25:28.902 --> 25:30.946
I offered to take care of her dog.

25:33.949 --> 25:34.866
Is that so?

25:36.159 --> 25:39.287
I don't know where I can lend more money.

25:40.538 --> 25:41.957
I'll also look into it for you.

25:42.499 --> 25:45.752
I'm so sorry for causing you
so much trouble.

25:45.835 --> 25:48.088
-It's nothing.
-I only used it once.

25:48.171 --> 25:50.340
-It's in absolute mint condition.
-Jae-hun.

25:50.423 --> 25:51.675
Please hold on.

25:51.758 --> 25:53.635
-Hello.
-Why are you outside?

25:53.718 --> 25:56.096
There were some other visitors inside.

25:57.138 --> 25:58.556
-Ma'am.
-Yes?

25:58.640 --> 26:01.142
The doctor came to check on Bom earlier.

26:01.726 --> 26:05.146
Bom told him she hurt herself by accident.

26:05.230 --> 26:07.941
Goodness, gracious. My baby.

26:08.024 --> 26:11.653
ANGOK HOSPITAL

26:11.736 --> 26:14.698
You should be grateful
that it wasn't any worse.

26:15.740 --> 26:17.200
Here, eat this.

26:19.995 --> 26:22.914
-Come on. Eat it.
-Give it to me.

26:25.458 --> 26:27.168
You've never been in surgery.

26:27.252 --> 26:29.129
Were you not scared during anesthesia?

26:30.171 --> 26:31.131
No.

26:32.215 --> 26:35.010
Did her dad go into rehab
without causing any commotion?

26:36.136 --> 26:37.220
Oh, yes.

26:38.054 --> 26:40.432
What do you mean, rehab?

26:41.599 --> 26:43.018
Well, Jeong-hun…

26:43.101 --> 26:45.562
He always turned a deaf ear
whenever we told him to go.

26:46.062 --> 26:48.523
He must have been
really spooked this time.

26:49.190 --> 26:52.068
Hey, that's no way to talk about your…

26:54.070 --> 26:56.114
Gosh. Yeong-suk

26:57.240 --> 26:58.533
Are you okay?

26:59.951 --> 27:01.244
Seong-min.

27:01.328 --> 27:04.122
Jeong-hun made it into rehab.
You don't have to worry.

27:04.622 --> 27:05.665
Thank you.

27:06.166 --> 27:08.418
You're always helping me out.

27:08.501 --> 27:10.420
-I owe you.
-Don't say that.

27:10.503 --> 27:13.131
It's a government rehab program,
so it's free.

27:13.214 --> 27:15.633
-So don't worry about it.
-That's great.

27:19.387 --> 27:20.430
Bom.

27:21.514 --> 27:22.724
I'm sorry.

27:24.059 --> 27:25.518
My baby.

27:29.230 --> 27:32.150
Words cannot express how sorry
and thankful I am.

27:32.734 --> 27:36.404
Come on, Yeong-suk.

27:36.946 --> 27:40.575
Things will look brighter from now on.

27:42.827 --> 27:45.747
ANGOK HOSPITAL

27:49.376 --> 27:50.377
Yeo-reum.

27:52.379 --> 27:53.421
Yes?

27:54.672 --> 27:57.717
Now you know what my life is really like.

27:59.219 --> 28:00.261
I guess so.

28:02.972 --> 28:04.099
I hate it.

28:09.020 --> 28:11.815
I can't take back what I've already seen.

28:12.649 --> 28:15.902
I was really hoping
you'd never see my dad.

28:21.408 --> 28:23.326
Remember what you asked me last time?

28:24.119 --> 28:26.246
If I had any moments
I'd like to go back to.

28:33.670 --> 28:35.046
When we were young,

28:36.423 --> 28:39.718
Ha-neul and I spent our days
counting the days

28:40.593 --> 28:42.053
until our Dad came home.

28:43.138 --> 28:45.515
-I'm home!
-Dad!

28:47.684 --> 28:48.977
Dad…

28:49.602 --> 28:53.523
worked in another region
and only came home once or twice a year.

28:55.191 --> 28:58.486
I used to cherish that day

28:59.320 --> 29:00.947
more than any holiday

29:02.073 --> 29:03.575
and even my birthday.

29:13.126 --> 29:14.669
These motherfuckers.

29:15.420 --> 29:16.921
Do they think I'm a pushover?

29:17.589 --> 29:19.174
-I'll fucking kill them all.
-Jeong-hun.

29:19.924 --> 29:21.217
-Damn it.
-Hey.

29:21.301 --> 29:22.635
-What are you holding in your hand?
-Those fuckers.

29:22.719 --> 29:24.888
-They're dead.
-What are you doing right now?

29:24.971 --> 29:26.556
Dad, what are you doing?

29:26.639 --> 29:28.349
-Fucking let go!
-Stop it!

29:28.433 --> 29:29.726
Put it down!

29:29.809 --> 29:30.894
I said put it down!

29:30.977 --> 29:32.395
Put it down!

29:32.479 --> 29:34.481
-Damn you!
-Put it down!

29:40.570 --> 29:43.323
I used to love going to
comic book stores with my dad.

29:47.368 --> 29:48.369
But…

29:50.330 --> 29:53.082
it wasn't the comics that I liked.

29:56.628 --> 29:57.837
I liked it because…

30:00.089 --> 30:02.425
I got to hold hands with my dad
on the way there.

30:34.958 --> 30:36.501
What the fuck did you just do?

30:37.085 --> 30:38.294
What do we do?

30:38.378 --> 30:39.796
My goodness.

30:41.381 --> 30:43.007
Ha-neul, your shoes!

30:43.508 --> 30:44.884
That's how it used to be.

30:45.552 --> 30:48.930
-Ha-neul, put your shoes on!
-That's what my dad used to be like.

30:57.146 --> 30:58.231
Bom.

31:00.692 --> 31:04.112
Get well quickly.
Make sure you eat well too.

31:05.488 --> 31:07.740
What about the hospital bill?

31:07.824 --> 31:09.951
That's not for you to worry about.

31:11.202 --> 31:13.663
Should I just tell them the truth?

31:14.622 --> 31:17.834
I have no idea what I should do.

31:18.793 --> 31:21.713
This is driving me crazy.

31:30.513 --> 31:34.517
ANGOK HOSPITAL

31:47.155 --> 31:50.033
You know Bom, right? Jeong-hun's daughter.

31:50.116 --> 31:52.327
Anyway, this is for her hospital bill,

31:52.410 --> 31:55.204
so let's talk over a meal
sometime this week.

31:55.288 --> 31:57.498
Goodbye. Okay.

31:58.666 --> 32:02.420
This punk. I know you sold
a plot of land recently, you cheapskate.

32:02.503 --> 32:06.549
How come the people of this town
care less about Bom than an outsider?

32:06.633 --> 32:08.134
Let's see. Who else can I call?

32:13.056 --> 32:14.474
So…

32:15.266 --> 32:19.562
I was wondering
if I could get the rent money back.

32:20.188 --> 32:21.022
What?

32:21.105 --> 32:23.399
Your rent? Why all of a sudden?

32:24.233 --> 32:27.278
I can move out as soon as I get it.

32:27.362 --> 32:31.282
You didn't even budge
when I tried to kick you out before.

32:33.618 --> 32:36.913
Is this about Bom's hospital bill?

32:37.705 --> 32:38.748
Not at all.

32:39.999 --> 32:41.376
I knew it.

32:42.043 --> 32:43.378
Gosh.

32:43.461 --> 32:47.757
But I'll have to discuss this with my dad,

32:47.840 --> 32:50.510
so let's talk
at the hospital tomorrow, okay?

32:51.260 --> 32:52.261
-Okay.
-Okay.

32:52.971 --> 32:54.347
Put in a good word for me.

32:54.430 --> 32:56.140
Sure. Don't worry.

32:56.724 --> 32:57.934
-Thank you.
-Bye.

33:13.032 --> 33:14.200
Gyeo-ul!

33:14.283 --> 33:15.910
I'm back!

33:17.412 --> 33:20.790
Sorry to keep you waiting all this time.

33:20.873 --> 33:23.292
You must've really missed me.

33:23.376 --> 33:24.460
Gyeo-ul.

33:25.294 --> 33:26.587
Hello.

33:27.880 --> 33:29.132
Hello.

33:29.632 --> 33:31.718
Gyeo-ul, let's go for a walk.

33:31.801 --> 33:32.885
Here.

33:34.595 --> 33:38.182
-I think he likes you more than me now.
-Come on.

33:38.266 --> 33:40.476
No way, I think he's just a friendly dog.

33:43.980 --> 33:45.189
What about Bom?

33:46.691 --> 33:48.526
She'll be going home tomorrow.

33:48.609 --> 33:49.777
What a relief.

33:51.863 --> 33:55.450
Then will you be coming to get
Gyeo-ul tomorrow?

33:55.533 --> 33:59.245
I found some toys for him,
so you can take them with you.

34:04.500 --> 34:05.585
Well…

34:06.919 --> 34:08.087
By any chance,

34:09.172 --> 34:13.468
Could you take care of Gyeo-ul?

34:15.011 --> 34:17.638
I think I'll have to…

34:57.678 --> 34:59.347
I liked it here.

35:29.836 --> 35:32.171
PROFESSOR LEE CHEOL-UNG

35:35.591 --> 35:37.176
ALTTEUL STORE

35:37.260 --> 35:39.971
You know Mr. Bong from downtown, right?

35:40.555 --> 35:42.640
He asked me
if the building is up for sale.

35:42.723 --> 35:44.392
Really?

35:45.643 --> 35:46.644
Hello.

35:46.727 --> 35:47.854
-Hey.
-Hey.

35:48.354 --> 35:49.856
-Hey, you punk.
-What?

35:49.939 --> 35:52.024
Where are you always wandering off to?

35:52.608 --> 35:54.944
I hear you've been going to
the hospital to see Bom.

35:55.528 --> 35:57.488
What? That's not true.

35:58.197 --> 36:01.159
If you want to sell it at market price,
you should wait it out.

36:01.242 --> 36:04.579
After seeing the graffiti,
I think I should sell it while I can.

36:05.163 --> 36:07.165
So you should go downtown

36:07.248 --> 36:09.167
and sound out what Bong thinks.

36:12.420 --> 36:13.713
What are you doing?

36:13.796 --> 36:14.630
What?

36:14.714 --> 36:16.048
What are you doing?

36:17.758 --> 36:20.553
I wanted to give you some allowance.

36:20.636 --> 36:21.846
Like this.

36:21.929 --> 36:23.306
Oh, no. You got me.

36:23.389 --> 36:26.601
How is it allowance when you just
put my money back into the wallet?

36:27.185 --> 36:28.436
What do you mean?

36:28.519 --> 36:31.230
I put my money in your wallet.

36:31.814 --> 36:35.026
If you keep talking nonsense,
you won't be getting any allowance.

36:35.109 --> 36:36.694
I'm leaving!

36:37.862 --> 36:39.739
He's done something again.

36:40.323 --> 36:42.116
I can tell just by looking at you.

36:42.200 --> 36:43.951
Let's see.

36:47.079 --> 36:48.539
I knew it.

36:48.623 --> 36:53.169
Of all the credit cards,
he took the one with the lowest limit.

36:53.669 --> 36:55.421
Gosh, that idiot.

36:56.505 --> 36:57.798
Goodness.

36:58.925 --> 36:59.926
Yes.

37:00.009 --> 37:01.844
-You're the guardian?
-Yes.

37:01.928 --> 37:04.305
I'm here for Kim Bom's discharge today.

37:04.388 --> 37:05.640
Just a moment, please.

37:09.185 --> 37:11.687
This is 4.13 million won.

37:11.771 --> 37:13.147
I can only pay this much right--

37:13.231 --> 37:15.191
It's Kim Bom in the surgical ward, right?

37:15.274 --> 37:16.651
HOSPITAL ADMINISTRATION

37:16.734 --> 37:17.818
Yes.

37:17.902 --> 37:19.278
The bill's already been paid.

37:20.112 --> 37:21.113
Sorry?

37:21.697 --> 37:23.115
There's nothing to pay for.

37:25.284 --> 37:26.577
Who paid?

37:26.661 --> 37:28.162
We don't know that.

37:28.246 --> 37:29.664
Next in line, please.

37:32.250 --> 37:33.292
Hello.

37:34.543 --> 37:35.670
Excuse me!

37:36.337 --> 37:38.130
You should take your money.

37:48.391 --> 37:49.892
Who could it be?

37:51.477 --> 37:53.312
Are you sure you're not lying to us?

37:55.147 --> 37:57.233
I wish I could have paid for it,

37:57.984 --> 37:59.193
but I don't have the money.

38:00.945 --> 38:04.073
Maybe the people in town helped out
because your grandma is so kind.

38:04.156 --> 38:05.157
-Right?
-Hey.

38:05.241 --> 38:06.909
No one in our town would do such a thing.

38:07.910 --> 38:10.538
I don't know what to say. I'm so grateful.

38:11.789 --> 38:14.041
-How could this happen?
-Gosh.

38:14.125 --> 38:15.584
You must be going home now, Bom.

38:16.502 --> 38:17.628
-Mr. Bae.
-Yes?

38:18.671 --> 38:20.464
By any chance…

38:20.548 --> 38:21.674
By any chance?

38:22.591 --> 38:23.801
You're right.

38:23.884 --> 38:25.761
Do you want to see what I brought?

38:27.305 --> 38:28.306
Ta-da!

38:29.682 --> 38:30.933
You can use this, ma'am.

38:31.017 --> 38:33.019
Buy the kids something delicious.

38:34.145 --> 38:35.104
Seong-min.

38:35.187 --> 38:36.731
Thank you so much.

38:37.982 --> 38:39.442
This is a total plot twist.

38:39.525 --> 38:41.736
What happened? What plot twist?

38:41.819 --> 38:43.112
What's up with you all?

38:43.195 --> 38:45.364
Did you pay the hospital bill?

38:45.448 --> 38:47.992
Me? The hospital bill?

38:49.285 --> 38:51.287
-It must not be him.
-What happened?

38:51.370 --> 38:53.372
Did someone pay for it?

38:53.456 --> 38:56.500
Yeo-reum says someone came in earlier
and paid the bill.

38:56.584 --> 38:58.127
Are you sure it's not you?

38:58.210 --> 39:01.589
It's not me. I just came in
after I stole my dad's card.

39:01.672 --> 39:03.424
So it's really not you?

39:03.507 --> 39:06.177
Why do you keep asking?
It's making me feel awkward.

39:06.761 --> 39:08.012
Then who could it be?

39:09.305 --> 39:10.431
Who could it be?

39:18.647 --> 39:19.607
Hello.

39:20.733 --> 39:21.734
Hello.

39:30.034 --> 39:32.244
Thank you for the books.

39:32.328 --> 39:33.412
-No problem.
-Thank you.

39:34.830 --> 39:37.917
How did you pick out
all the books that I wanted to read?

39:38.501 --> 39:40.294
Did I? I'm glad to hear that.

39:42.630 --> 39:46.801
By the way, what will happen to Gyeo-ul?

39:49.303 --> 39:50.346
I think…

39:52.098 --> 39:55.142
he'll be staying with me.

39:58.729 --> 39:59.855
Is that okay with you?

40:00.648 --> 40:01.941
Of course.

40:12.076 --> 40:13.494
You should say goodbye.

40:15.246 --> 40:16.372
Say "Thank you."

40:17.081 --> 40:18.833
-Goodbye.
-"Goodbye."

40:20.209 --> 40:23.379
I'll write up a story
about the lady we interviewed

40:23.462 --> 40:26.090
and send it to you.

40:26.173 --> 40:27.258
Sure.

40:27.883 --> 40:30.845
These are toys for Gyeo-ul.

40:31.345 --> 40:32.972
I bought these for him.

40:35.266 --> 40:36.350
Thank you.

40:37.226 --> 40:39.979
I've never bought anything
like this for him.

40:41.480 --> 40:43.232
You must be happy, Gyeo-ul.

40:47.027 --> 40:49.071
By the way,

40:49.780 --> 40:52.199
-are you free--
-Gosh.

40:52.283 --> 40:53.742
You're finally going home today.

40:53.826 --> 40:55.161
Hello.

40:55.953 --> 40:57.413
Bom must have been discharged.

40:57.496 --> 40:59.415
I heard you took care of her every day.

40:59.498 --> 41:02.877
It was nothing. How have you been?

41:03.461 --> 41:05.838
It's the same old for us.
Boring and uneventful.

41:06.922 --> 41:08.799
I'm glad you're taking him back today.

41:08.883 --> 41:10.509
Dae-bum is going to Seoul tomorrow.

41:11.218 --> 41:12.470
I see.

41:12.553 --> 41:15.097
-He's going to Seoul.
-Yes.

41:15.181 --> 41:16.891
I have an interview tomorrow,

41:16.974 --> 41:18.809
and he offered to drive me.

41:18.893 --> 41:21.103
I see. An interview.

41:22.229 --> 41:24.607
Weren't you about to say something?

41:26.025 --> 41:27.067
It's nothing.

41:27.610 --> 41:29.361
We're not opening tomorrow.

41:29.445 --> 41:30.488
All right.

41:31.405 --> 41:33.115
Have a safe trip to Seoul.

41:33.199 --> 41:34.241
-Goodbye.
-Goodbye.

41:34.325 --> 41:35.242
Bye.

41:35.743 --> 41:37.411
You take care too.

41:39.455 --> 41:41.332
That's a weight off your shoulders.

41:42.249 --> 41:44.084
It's not easy to look after a dog.

41:47.254 --> 41:49.089
Now that I think about it,

41:49.173 --> 41:53.219
I do kind of miss him from time to time.

41:54.512 --> 41:57.765
I hurt my leg two years ago,

41:58.516 --> 42:03.896
so I used to go to a hospital in Seoul
to get treatment.

42:05.481 --> 42:08.901
But it didn't get any better.

42:10.903 --> 42:13.489
I hurt my leg two years ago,

42:14.698 --> 42:19.495
so I used to go to a hospital in Seoul
to get treatment.

42:21.330 --> 42:24.333
But it didn't get any better.

42:25.292 --> 42:29.505
GRADE 7 PUBLIC SERVANT INTERVIEW HALL

42:30.881 --> 42:33.759
Ji-yeong. Good luck with your interview.

42:34.426 --> 42:35.469
Thank you.

42:37.096 --> 42:40.349
And I have to meet someone. I'll be back.

42:41.016 --> 42:42.101
Who?

42:45.062 --> 42:47.147
-The professor?
-You don't need to know.

42:47.231 --> 42:49.483
-You're going to be late. Hurry on in.
-All right.

42:49.567 --> 42:50.693
Good luck.

42:50.776 --> 42:52.319
-Let's talk after.
-Okay.

42:52.403 --> 42:53.821
-I'll get going.
-Bye.

42:56.907 --> 42:58.158
Yeo-reum.

43:02.204 --> 43:03.247
Yeo-reum.

43:03.956 --> 43:04.999
What?

43:05.833 --> 43:07.209
Where is she?

43:08.085 --> 43:09.211
Yeo-reum.

43:17.553 --> 43:18.721
Hello?

43:18.804 --> 43:20.556
Yeo-reum, where are you?

43:20.639 --> 43:23.309
I'm on the rooftop hanging my laundry.

43:23.392 --> 43:25.269
Can you come and give me a hand?

43:25.352 --> 43:26.312
The rooftop?

43:27.438 --> 43:30.065
I see. All right, I'll be there.

43:33.360 --> 43:35.529
What are you doing up here?

43:35.613 --> 43:37.239
I've been waiting for you.

43:37.323 --> 43:38.907
It was empty downstairs.

43:38.991 --> 43:40.326
Heads-up!

43:42.036 --> 43:43.662
Are you nuts, Jae-hun?

43:43.746 --> 43:46.373
-Gosh, look at her face.
-One, two, three!

43:46.457 --> 43:48.792
Congratulations on coming home, Bom!

43:48.876 --> 43:51.003
Let's please live a mellow life
from now on.

43:51.086 --> 43:54.006
Hey, Heo Jae-hun! What did you just do?

43:54.089 --> 43:55.299
Come here.

43:55.382 --> 43:57.551
-Come here, let's wipe it off.
-Gosh, seriously.

43:57.635 --> 43:59.803
-Come take a seat.
-Darn you.

43:59.887 --> 44:01.096
My eyes.

44:01.180 --> 44:02.598
-Are you okay?
-Let's wipe that.

44:02.681 --> 44:04.183
Do you have a death wish, Jae-hun?

44:04.266 --> 44:06.477
You'll have to wash your face.

44:08.103 --> 44:09.229
Oh, what's all this?

44:09.813 --> 44:12.107
This party is sponsored by Altteul Store.

44:12.191 --> 44:13.525
It's sick, right?

44:15.152 --> 44:16.612
How do you like it?

44:17.196 --> 44:19.448
Did you prepare all this?

44:19.531 --> 44:20.783
Of course. We did everything.

44:21.367 --> 44:24.453
We all got together to prepare this.

44:26.955 --> 44:28.916
But what's that in your hand?

44:28.999 --> 44:32.002
I heard Yeo-reum likes chicken,
so I brought some.

44:32.086 --> 44:34.171
-Really?
-I can never allow that.

44:34.254 --> 44:35.673
You just got discharged,

44:35.756 --> 44:37.257
so you can't have fried chicken.

44:37.341 --> 44:38.884
You can eat what I made.

44:38.967 --> 44:41.053
What did you make?

44:41.136 --> 44:42.888
It's called chicken noodle soup.

44:42.971 --> 44:44.682
It's what they eat in the US
when they get sick.

44:44.765 --> 44:46.350
You have to have it.

44:46.433 --> 44:47.810
It's the same chicken anyway.

44:47.893 --> 44:49.186
What? It's not the same.

44:49.269 --> 44:50.479
-I'll eat it then.
-You can't either.

44:50.562 --> 44:52.106
I'll throw it so no one will eat it.

44:52.189 --> 44:54.274
-No, my chicken!
-Gosh.

44:54.858 --> 44:56.151
You're a lunatic.

44:56.235 --> 44:57.653
You need to be taught a lesson.

44:57.736 --> 44:59.405
-Come here!
-I told you not to eat it.

44:59.488 --> 45:01.949
-What a waste of chicken.
-Seriously, Heo Jae-hun!

45:29.726 --> 45:32.688
This is good for the liver,
so make sure you eat everything.

45:33.188 --> 45:34.481
Gosh, you little brat.

45:34.565 --> 45:36.525
I'll let this slide
since it's a happy day.

45:40.737 --> 45:42.156
-Yeo-reum.
-Yes?

45:43.073 --> 45:46.034
To be honest, I've never done
something like this before.

45:46.118 --> 45:47.870
-Really?
-Yes.

45:49.371 --> 45:50.456
Me neither.

45:50.539 --> 45:51.582
Really?

45:54.585 --> 45:55.669
Hey…

45:56.545 --> 45:57.921
Thank you, Yeo-reum.

45:59.631 --> 46:02.926
All I did was let them use the rooftop.

46:04.011 --> 46:07.473
Whatever happens,
I'll repay what you did for me.

46:07.556 --> 46:11.268
Even my grandma said
that she'll give you kimchi forever.

46:15.439 --> 46:17.900
But the one who paid the bill wasn't me.

46:19.943 --> 46:23.071
Come on, everyone drink up your sodas!

46:23.155 --> 46:25.574
I thought it was him.

46:26.200 --> 46:27.951
What are you talking about?

46:28.952 --> 46:30.245
Someone has a crush on me again?

46:30.329 --> 46:31.705
I don't think it's him.

46:31.788 --> 46:34.374
Yeo-reum. Are you sure
you're not putting on an act?

46:34.458 --> 46:37.336
-It's really not me.
-So? Who's the one with the crush?

46:37.419 --> 46:38.545
Here.

46:38.629 --> 46:40.797
The chicken noodle soup is ready.

46:44.176 --> 46:46.678
The food is all ready. When is he coming?

46:46.762 --> 46:48.889
What? Who else is coming?

46:48.972 --> 46:52.267
Dae-bum. I told him
we're having a party here today.

46:52.351 --> 46:55.270
What are you saying?
Dae-bum went to Seoul with Ji-yeong today.

46:55.354 --> 46:57.523
Really? He should have come here.

46:58.232 --> 46:59.316
Tell me about it.

46:59.399 --> 47:02.569
Dae-bum and Ji-yeong are always together.

47:03.111 --> 47:07.032
I'm a better driver than Dae-bum.
Don't you agree?

47:07.616 --> 47:09.576
Why are you taking it out on me?

47:11.453 --> 47:14.248
-Let's dig in.
-So this is the soup you talked about?

47:14.331 --> 47:15.290
Yes.

47:15.832 --> 47:17.501
It looks funny.

47:17.584 --> 47:20.295
It looks like chicken kalguksu.

47:20.796 --> 47:21.838
You're right.

47:21.922 --> 47:24.675
Isn't it just chicken kalguksu
made with pasta noodles?

47:25.259 --> 47:26.843
Fine. I'll just throw this away too.

47:26.927 --> 47:28.095
-No!
-Stop it!

47:29.721 --> 47:30.889
Hey, Dae-bum.

47:31.682 --> 47:35.143
There's still so much
I don't know about you.

47:35.978 --> 47:36.937
What?

47:37.521 --> 47:39.022
What do you mean?

47:41.024 --> 47:42.943
How did the interview go?

47:43.527 --> 47:46.238
No. My interview isn't the issue here.

47:46.321 --> 47:51.201
I thought you were a different person,
watching you solve equations.

47:51.285 --> 47:53.412
You shouldn't be rotting away in Angok.

47:53.495 --> 47:57.374
I was born to live in Angok.

47:58.083 --> 47:59.167
Even my last name sounds like An.

48:00.711 --> 48:03.338
To be frank,
I sometimes looked down on you.

48:03.422 --> 48:04.339
Sure.

48:05.090 --> 48:07.092
I'm so ashamed about feeling that way.

48:08.343 --> 48:10.053
That's what I like about you.

48:10.721 --> 48:12.973
Hey, drop the sarcasm.

48:13.849 --> 48:14.933
You little…

48:20.022 --> 48:22.065
-Man, I'm full.
-I'm so full.

48:22.149 --> 48:23.734
This dish is really interesting.

48:23.817 --> 48:26.570
-It tasted better than I thought, Jae-hun.
-I told you.

48:27.154 --> 48:28.030
All right.

48:28.614 --> 48:30.115
-Shall we clean up?
-Sure, let's do that.

48:30.198 --> 48:31.074
Wait.

48:31.158 --> 48:34.077
Now that we're all full,
we need to digest the food.

48:34.161 --> 48:36.330
-Right. Of course we should.
-Yes, that's right.

48:36.413 --> 48:37.247
What's going on?

48:37.331 --> 48:38.540
-I don't know.
-You don't know either?

48:38.624 --> 48:41.460
-Are you ready?
-They must have prepared something.

48:41.543 --> 48:42.878
-I'm curious.
-What is it?

48:46.256 --> 48:49.301
-What's wrong with him?
-Give me a round of applause.

48:49.384 --> 48:50.969
Gosh, this is so embarrassing.

48:54.890 --> 48:56.099
You're good at that!

48:56.183 --> 48:57.184
No, I can't.

48:57.768 --> 48:59.019
Come on!

48:59.645 --> 49:01.521
Come hold my hand, Yeo-reum.

49:04.149 --> 49:05.859
Here are your presents.

49:05.942 --> 49:07.527
Gosh, this is so pretty.

49:07.611 --> 49:09.154
It's beautiful.

49:14.159 --> 49:15.577
-Yeo-reum.
-Yes?

49:16.953 --> 49:18.330
Thank you.

49:18.413 --> 49:19.956
I told you it wasn't me.

49:21.583 --> 49:25.545
Thanks to you, I feel happier now.

49:27.547 --> 49:28.590
Really?

49:29.675 --> 49:30.926
Yes.

49:33.011 --> 49:34.471
Why are you just standing there?

49:34.554 --> 49:36.056
Hey!

50:02.499 --> 50:04.042
I'm speeding up.

50:43.749 --> 50:46.460
Shall we meet at the library
every morning for a jog?

50:46.543 --> 50:48.128
-Do you want to see a movie?
-Chicken and beer?

50:48.211 --> 50:49.588
Ji-yeong, that hurts.

50:50.213 --> 50:53.008
I'm also starting to hurt because of you.

50:53.091 --> 50:56.219
Our bodies are smart.
They don't forget traumas so easily.

50:56.303 --> 50:57.846
-Dae-bum!
-He held onto his life

50:57.929 --> 50:59.848
trying his best not to break down.

50:59.931 --> 51:01.641
But all of that fell apart today.

51:02.225 --> 51:04.436
Can you take responsibility
for Dae-bum's life?

51:04.978 --> 51:06.396
I can.

51:06.480 --> 51:10.066
For you, this might be
just a summer fling by the beach,

51:10.150 --> 51:11.693
but that's not the case for me.

51:11.777 --> 51:14.571
Subtitle translation by: Jea-Heon Chung
